# M100 P3 — keep local dev artifacts out of the production image build.
#
# Critical: Vite reads .env.local at build time. The dev .env.local pins
# VITE_LINK_* to localhost:<port> (split-origin dev), which would OVERRIDE the
# same-origin '/workflow' etc. defaults in src/lib/env.ts and bake the old
# cross-app links into the shipped bundle. Excluding env files here lets the
# image build fall back to the same-origin defaults. Runtime overrides (if a
# split-origin deployment needs them) are passed as build args / env, not files.
node_modules
dist
.git
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.log
